 period. The Observatory also pioneered in using the talents of women, several of whom became noted astronomers, and their monumental classification of stars from spectral records constitutes a fundamental contribution to astronomical knowledge. The authors vividly portray the genesis, growth, and achievements of a major scientific institution and its relations with other observatories. Through the use of photographs and correspondence they also portray the men and women who played essential roles in the development of astronomy in the nineteenth and early twentieth centuries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAstronomie, Kartografie. 4aHarvard College Observatory -- History. 4aSCIENCE / Astronomy. 4aSCIENCE / General. 4aSCIENCE / History. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / New England (CT, MA, ME, NH, RI, VT).2bisacsh1 aBoyd, Lyle Gifford, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMenzel, Donald H.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: American History eBook Packagez9783110353464oZDB-23-HAH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Complete eBook Packagez9783110353488oZDB-23-HCO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z97831104422120 cprintz978067441878340uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.978067441880640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674418806423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674418806.jpg  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-HAH  aZDB-23-HCO